  "text": "As the variables used for segmentation are usually derived from demographics, behaviour, psychographics or geographic [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , criteria that are employed by the wine industry can be related to the four classic market segmentation bases . These are geographic, i.e. country or city where the customer lives, demographic, i.e. age, gender, income and social class, psychographic, i.e. lifestyles and personality,",
